Class Street

  • java.lang.Object
    • tp.pr5.Street
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MockStreet

    public class Street
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    A street links two places A and B. All streets are two-way streets.
    If a street is defined as Street(A,NORTH,B) this means that Place B is at NORTH of Place A and Place A is at south of Place B
    Author:
    Abel Serrano Juste

      • open

        public boolean open(CodeCard card)
        Try to open a street using a code card. Codes must match in order to complete this action
        It only works when the street is closed
        Parameters:
        card - A code card to open the street
        Returns:
        true if the street has been opened with the codecard.
        Note that if the street isn't closed or it isn't the incorrect code, this return false

      • close

        public boolean close(CodeCard card)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
